title: Air Knowledge
description: AirKnowledge is a partnership training program in                  the U.S. Environmental Protection Agency’s (EPA’s) Office of                  Air Quality Planning and Standards (OAQPS). AirKnowledge                  develops training material focused on the Clean Air Act                  program areas managed by OAQPS. This website is intended for                  use by the public and EPA staff.

title: AirNow Fire and Smoke Map
description: This map shows fine particle pollution (PM2.5) from wildfires and other sources. It provides a public resource of information to best prepare and manage wildfire season. Developed in a joint partnership between the EPA and USFS.
keywords: Wildfire, Smoke, Air Quality, Protective Actions, PM2.5
